<h4 id="how-to-unset-single-bit-in-a-byte">How to unset single bit in a byte?</h4>

<p>For e.g In byte 0100 1000 unset bit no 6 will produce 0000 1000<br />
(Remember bit number starts with 0-7)</p>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><figcaption class='code-header'><span>Unset Bit </span></figcaption>
 <div class="CodeRay">
  <div class="code"><pre><span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n1" name="n1">1</a></span>
<span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n2" name="n2">2</a></span><span style="color:#777">//To unset specific bit we will use (AND) operation.</span>
<span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n3" name="n3">3</a></span><span style="color:#777">//Mask value need to be ‘0’ for the bit to unset but rest of the bits</span>
<span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n4" name="n4">4</a></span><span style="color:#777">//need to ‘1’. The reason for rest of the bits to set as ‘1’ is as</span>
<span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n5" name="n5">5</a></span><span style="color:#777">//we are doing (AND), we don’t want to unset other bits which are</span>
<span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n6" name="n6">6</a></span><span style="color:#777">//already set.</span>
<span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n7" name="n7">7</a></span><span style="color:#777">//</span>
<span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n8" name="n8">8</a></span><span style="color:#777">//For e.g.</span>
<span class="line-numbers"> <a href="#n9" name="n9">9</a></span><span style="color:#777">//To unset 6th bit 0100 1000</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><strong><a href="#n10" name="n10">10</a></strong></span><span style="color:#777">//            MASK 1011 1111 (AND)</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n11" name="n11">11</a></span><span style="color:#777">//                ——————————-</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n12" name="n12">12</a></span><span style="color:#777">//                 0000 1000   (Result)</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n13" name="n13">13</a></span><span style="color:#0a8;font-weight:bold">int</span> unset-bit(<span style="color:#0a8;font-weight:bold">int</span> val, <span style="color:#0a8;font-weight:bold">int</span> num, <span style="color:#0a8;font-weight:bold">bool</span> bitval)
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n14" name="n14">14</a></span>{
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n15" name="n15">15</a></span>    <span style="color:#080;font-weight:bold">return</span> (val &amp;amp; ~(bitval <span style="color:#F00;background-color:#FAA">«</span><span style="color:#F00;background-color:#FAA"> </span>num));
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n16" name="n16">16</a></span>}&lt;/p&gt;
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n17" name="n17">17</a></span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n18" name="n18">18</a></span>&lt;p&gt;<span style="color:#777">//Here, val    = 0100 1000</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n19" name="n19">19</a></span><span style="color:#777">//      num    = 6</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><strong><a href="#n20" name="n20">20</a></strong></span><span style="color:#777">//      bitval = 0</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n21" name="n21">21</a></span><span style="color:#777">//      (bitval « num) = 0100 0000</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n22" name="n22">22</a></span><span style="color:#777">//     ~(bitval « num) = 1011 1111</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n23" name="n23">23</a></span><span style="color:#777">//</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n24" name="n24">24</a></span><span style="color:#777">//      0100 1000</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n25" name="n25">25</a></span><span style="color:#777">//      1011 1111 (AND)</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n26" name="n26">26</a></span><span style="color:#777">//      —————————-</span>
<span class="line-numbers"><a href="#n27" name="n27">27</a></span><span style="color:#777">//      0000 1000    (Result)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
 </figure></notextile></div></p>

